  12:../../libs/PoliTeKDSP/libs/libDaisy/src/per/dac.h ****  ** For now only Normal Mode is supported,
  13:../../libs/PoliTeKDSP/libs/libDaisy/src/per/dac.h ****  ** Sample and hold mode provides reduced power consumption, but requires a bit more setup.
  14:../../libs/PoliTeKDSP/libs/libDaisy/src/per/dac.h ****  **
  15:../../libs/PoliTeKDSP/libs/libDaisy/src/per/dac.h ****  ** For now connecting the DAC through other internal peripherals is also not supported.
  16:../../libs/PoliTeKDSP/libs/libDaisy/src/per/dac.h ****  **
  17:../../libs/PoliTeKDSP/libs/libDaisy/src/per/dac.h ****  ** Since the DAC channels have dedicated pins we don't need to pass in a pin config like with
  18:../../libs/PoliTeKDSP/libs/libDaisy/src/per/dac.h ****  ** other modules. However, it is still important to not try to use the DAC pins for anything else.
  19:../../libs/PoliTeKDSP/libs/libDaisy/src/per/dac.h ****  ** DAC Channel 1 is on PA4, and DAC Channel 2 is on PA5
  20:../../libs/PoliTeKDSP/libs/libDaisy/src/per/dac.h ****  ***/
